Hey Gene - the routing table is actually correct. Those directly connected routes (no gateway) are right for local subnet traffic. The return-path routing for cross-VLAN clients is handled by the source-based policy routing from the MachineConfigs (you can verify with ip rule list and ip route show table all on the masters). The real issue right now is that MetalLB speakers aren't binding VIPs to any interface at all - so routing doesn't even come into play yet. We're still digging into why the speaker announcer is broken
